THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 616C.180 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 616C.180 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section, an injury or
3 disease sustained by an employee that is caused by stress is compensable pursuant
4 to the provisions of chapters 616A to 616D, inclusive, or chapter 617 of NRS if it
5 arose out of and in the course of his or her employment.
6 2. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 4, any ailment or disorder
7 caused by any gradual mental stimulus, and any death or disability ensuing
8 therefrom, shall be deemed not to be an injury or disease arising out of and in the
9 course of employment.
10 3. Except as otherwise provided by subsections 4 and 5, an injury or disease
11 caused by stress shall be deemed to arise out of and in the course of employment
12 only if the employee proves by clear and convincing medical or psychiatric
13 evidence that:
14 (a) The employee has a mental injury caused by extreme stress in time of
15 danger;
16 (b) The primary cause of the injury was an event that arose out of and during
17 the course of his or her employment; and
18 (c) The stress was not caused by his or her layoff, the termination of his or her
19 employment or any disciplinary action taken against him or her.
20 4. An injury or disease caused by stress shall be deemed to arise out of and in
21 the course of employment if the employee is a first responder and proves by clear
22 and convincing medical or psychiatric evidence that:
23 (a) The employee has a mental injury caused by extreme stress due to the
24 employee directly witnessing:
25 (1) The death, or the aftermath of the death, of a person as a result of a
26 violent event, including, without limitation, a homicide, suicide or mass casualty
27 incident; or
28 (2) An injury, or the aftermath of an injury, that involves grievous bodily
29 harm of a nature that shocks the conscience; and
30 (b) The primary cause of the mental injury was the employee witnessing an
31 event or a series of events described in paragraph (a) during the course of his or her
32 employment.
33 5. An injury or disease caused by stress shall be deemed to arise out of and in
34 the course of employment, and shall not be deemed the result of gradual mental
35 stimulus, if the employee is employed by the State or any of its agencies or political
36 subdivisions and proves by clear and convincing medical or psychiatric evidence
37 that:
38 (a) The employee has a mental injury caused by extreme stress due to the
39 employee responding to a mass casualty incident; and
40 (b) The primary cause of the injury was the employee responding to the mass
41 casualty incident during the course of his or her employment.
42 6. An agency which employs a first responder, including, without limitation, a
43 first responder who serves as a volunteer, shall provide educational training to the

